                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client with Parkinson's disease. Which finding about gait would the nurse expect to note in the client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe parkinsonian gait is characterized by short, accelerating, shuffling steps. The client leans forward with the head, hips, and knees flexed and has difficulty starting and stopping. An ataxic gait is unsteady and staggering. A dystrophic gait is broad-based and waddling. Walking on the toes can occur from shortened Achilles tendons.",
                        "id": "88a917267efe468893933f165524cd4a",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ecf9e1b61a864553a2636c7f6c6191a5",
                                "content": "I can sit down to put on my pants and shoes."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9bc65ba6b143475d9cfb04e450a4dd39",
                                "content": "My family removed all loose rugs from my bedroom."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "4cbeb27ee0864edda50071ba91da2a73",
                                "content": "I try to exercise every day and rest when I'm tired."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b93b87d6f45a49b7af16f20532b7ba6f",
                                "content": "I don't need to use my walker to get to the bathroom."
                            }
